The paper proposes a novel framework for deep semi-supervised feature learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the use of Minor Constraint Disturbances (MCD) to improve the stability and reduce the reliance on labels in high-dimensional data space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
